# Admin (local & Vercel)

Create a `.env.local` file in the project root:

```env
SESSION_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-string-at-least-32-chars
ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
ADMIN_PASSWORD=choose-a-strong-password

# Multiple admins (optional) — single-line JSON; usernames must be unique.
# You can use this instead of ADMIN_USERNAME/ADMIN_PASSWORD, or together with them.
# ADMIN_USERS=[{"username":"admin","password":"one-secret"},{"username":"kevin","password":"another-secret"}]

# Local testing only — enables "Skip login" on /admin/login (never set on Vercel)
DEV_ADMIN_BYPASS=true
```

Optional for **persistent edits on Vercel** (serverless cannot write to disk):

```env
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=your_vercel_blob_token
```

Without Blob, production reads the committed `data/site-content.json`; admin saves work locally in development.

## URLs

- Public site: `/`
- Admin login (also linked in footer): `/admin/login`
- Dashboard (after login): `/admin/dashboard`
